06:50.570 --> 06:51.930
Uh, it doesn't look
like you got it

06:51.930 --> 06:53.700
in a magic shop,
and you didn't.

06:53.700 --> 06:56.300
Uh, this really looks
like something different.

06:56.300 --> 06:58.400
Also the effect,
and the whole way

06:58.400 --> 07:00.370
it's laid out
is very different

07:00.370 --> 07:01.770
than anything that we've seen.
It really is--

07:01.770 --> 07:03.330
It really is new, original.

07:03.330 --> 07:06.030
And your presentation
did not have a lot of jive

07:06.030 --> 07:07.300
and garbage.

07:07.300 --> 07:11.430
Just simple, straightforward,
sweet, and beautiful.

07:11.430 --> 07:14.900
And, um, we don't know
if we know how this is done.

07:14.900 --> 07:16.670
We really don't.
We've got--

07:16.670 --> 07:20.870
We know very few ways
to do, uh, levitations.

07:20.870 --> 07:23.230
There are just very few ways
that we know of.

07:23.230 --> 07:25.070
And, uh, the first thing
you might think of

07:25.070 --> 07:28.100
is some sort of, um, uh--
to make 'em float.

07:28.100 --> 07:29.900
You'd think about magnets,
but magnet stuff

07:29.900 --> 07:31.870
has to be spinning,
you know?

07:31.870 --> 07:34.000
We'd also think that maybe
it was attached to you,

07:34.000 --> 07:36.500
but it would be wiggling
in some way, you know?

07:36.500 --> 07:39.200
This was really secured,
really steady.

07:39.200 --> 07:41.970
And, um,
the one kind of, um,

07:41.970 --> 07:44.770
thread of an idea we had
was that, uh--

07:44.770 --> 07:47.000
was that the theater
