Penn, meanwhile,
he's burning the cards.

12:34.370 --> 12:36.270
He's looking at the corners
to make sure

12:36.270 --> 12:38.000
that I haven't
cut any of them

12:38.000 --> 12:39.970
to make them easier
to get to.

12:39.970 --> 12:41.900
Or, maybe I filed down
the edges

12:41.900 --> 12:45.030
in order to make one card
stand out from the others.

12:45.030 --> 12:47.200
Maybe--
Maybe I used glue,

12:47.200 --> 12:49.700
on the edges of my fingers
in order to make it easier

12:49.700 --> 12:50.900
to catch that card.

12:50.900 --> 12:52.300
That would be clever.

12:52.300 --> 12:53.670
Or better yet,

12:53.670 --> 12:56.470
I have magnets in my fingertips
that allow me

12:56.470 --> 12:58.400
to capture that card.
- Oh!

12:58.400 --> 13:00.300
- Yeah, maybe I do!
Maybe I do!

13:00.300 --> 13:01.600
Maybe I don't.

13:01.600 --> 13:03.130
That's not for me to say.

13:03.130 --> 13:06.630
So, all of these possibilities
are there for you to consider.

13:06.630 --> 13:07.970
Maybe I'm telling you
the truth,

13:07.970 --> 13:10.000
and maybe I'm not.
[audience laughter]

13:10.000 --> 13:11.270
Now, I know
that doesn't seem fair,

13:11.270 --> 13:13.300
but, hey,
you guys started this game.

13:13.300 --> 13:15.630
- [chuckles]
[audience laughter]

13:15.630 --> 13:19.270
- So here's
what I'm going to do.

13:19.270 --> 13:21.230
I'm going
to shuffle these cards,

13:21.230 --> 13:22.670
but I won't push them in
all the way,

13:22.670 --> 13:24.270
leaving some of these cards
isolated

13:24.270 --> 13:25.670
and out of my control.

13:25.670 --> 13:27.530
I'm also going
to riffle slowly,

13:27.530 --> 13:29.870
so Penn knows I'm not
influencing his choice

13:29.870 --> 13:32.100
with Jedi mind tricks.

13:32.100 --> 13:33.730
Penn, please say "stop."

13:33.730 --> 13:35.470
- Stop.
- Are you happy there?

13:35.470 --> 13:36.630
- One more.
- One more?

13:36.630 --> 13:37.870
How's that?
- Good.

13:37.870 --> 13:39.200
- Teller, you feeling good
about all this?

13:39.200 --> 13:41.070
Sure, why not, right?
Now, very important:

13:41.070 --> 13:42.530
Before we go any further,

13:42.530 --> 13:43.730
I want you to make sure
that your card

13:43.730 --> 13:45.300
is not near the top,
or near the bottom.

13:45.300 --> 13:46.570
That it's somewhere
within the spread.

13:46.570 --> 13:47.800
And Alyson, you can--
I'm sorry,

13:47.800 --> 13:49.530
you didn't see the card.
- No.

13:49.530 --> 13:50.930
- Now you know how I feel.
- Yeah!

13:50.930 --> 13:52.230
- [chuckles]
- Yeah!

13:52.230 --> 13:53.770
- So are--are you satisfied?

13:53.770 --> 13:56.300
It's in the spread, very good.

13:56.300 --> 13:58.930
Now, at this moment in time,
there are multiple realities

13:58.930 --> 13:59.970
happening here onstage.

13:59.970 --> 14:01.300
See, Penn and Teller,

14:01.300 --> 14:02.600
they're focused
on the method of the trick,

14:02.600 --> 14:04.670
and trying to figure out
what I lied to them about.

14:04.670 --> 14:07.300
But you and the audience,
you don't care about method,

14:07.300 --> 14:09.130
so you get
to experience the effect.

14:09.130 --> 14:10.270
- Yeah!
- Look at the joy

14:10.270 --> 14:11.730
on her face, right?
- Yeah, uh-huh.

14:11.730 --> 14:14.600
Now, whereas for you
the card shot out of the deck

14:14.600 --> 14:16.170
and I caught it
at my fingertips,

14:16.170 --> 14:18.770
for you gentlemen,
my fingers are going to shoot

14:18.770 --> 14:19.930
into the deck,

14:19.930 --> 14:22.170
and I will capture your card.

14:22.170 --> 14:23.770
[sighs]

14:33.000 --> 14:34.170
Penn, what was your card?

14:34.170 --> 14:36.600
- King of spades.

14:36.600 --> 14:38.170
- Your card.

14:38.170 --> 14:41.800
The king of spades.

14:41.800 --> 14:44.130
[cheers and applause]

14:44.130 --> 14:46.870
Thank you very much,
gentlemen!

14:46.870 --> 14:48.100
Thank you very much!

14:48.100 --> 14:49.930
- Kostya Kimlat!

14:49.930 --> 14:53.170
[cheers and applause]

14:53.170 --> 14:55.500
- I can understand
why he wanted to hit you.

14:55.500 --> 14:56.800
- [laughing] Yes!
- Yeah.

14:56.800 --> 14:58.800
That was incredible!
- Thank you so much.

14:58.800 --> 15:01.170
I'm--it's so frustrating
to not, like,

15:01.170 --> 15:02.830
know how you did that.
- Yeah, well,

15:02.830 --> 15:04.130
it's part of the magic,
part of the beauty of it.

15:04.130 --> 15:06.170
Mm-hmm.
- So, am I correct in thinking

15:06.170 --> 15:08.300
you've worked on that trick
for 17 years?

15:08.300 --> 15:10.270
- Yes, I've been practicing it
for 17 years.

15:10.270 --> 15:11.570
- Wow!
- Yes.

15:11.570 --> 15:13.530
- What was it at 17 years
you were like,

15:13.530 --> 15:15.500
"Yep, it's ready."
- You know, I just--

15:15.500 --> 15:17.170
No, I just had no life.
I always played with cards.

15:17.170 --> 15:19.430
I always went with my hand.
I'm always practicing.

15:19.430 --> 15:21.200
I created it to fool magicians.
- Yeah.

15:21.200 --> 15:22.430
- But I showed it
kind of underground,

15:22.430 --> 15:23.770
didn't show it
to too many people.

15:23.770 --> 15:25.330
And for three years now,
I've been thinking

15:25.330 --> 15:27.400
what I can do to come back.

15:27.400 --> 15:28.800
And I thought, "This is it."
- This is it.

15:28.800 --> 15:30.230
- Yeah!
- Oh!

15:30.230 --> 15:32.370
Was it nerve-racking coming
back for the second time?

15:32.370 --> 15:33.630
- I've been really
looking forward to it.

15:33.630 --> 15:34.900
I've been looking forward
to seeing their faces,

15:34.900 --> 15:36.670
and spending time with them
onstage here.

15:36.670 --> 15:38.630
So this has been the moment
that I'm really excited about.

15:38.630 --> 15:40.170
- And how has your life changed

15:40.170 --> 15:42.170
since you were on
the first time?

15:42.170 --> 15:43.670
- You know, the first time
I was on "Fool Us"--

15:43.670 --> 15:45.000
before then, no one knew
who I was,

15:45.000 --> 15:46.970
and didn't know I was coming,
but ever since then,

15:46.970 --> 15:48.630
it's changed my life,
because now people know,

15:48.630 --> 15:50.430
"Oh, you're the guy
that fooled Penn and Teller!

15:50.430 --> 15:52.600
Let's hire you!"
- Um...

15:52.600 --> 15:54.230
Okay, I...
- [nervous sigh]

15:54.230 --> 15:56.270
- I don't know,
I see some surprised looks.

15:56.270 --> 15:58.030
Let's talk to the boys.

15:58.030 --> 16:00.130
- 'Kay.
- Gentlemen.

16:00.130 --> 16:03.500
- I want you to think
about this, because, um...

16:03.500 --> 16:06.830
if we do this bust on you,

16:06.830 --> 16:08.630
and if we're wrong,

16:08.630 --> 16:11.430
and if you fooled us again,

16:11.430 --> 16:13.400
I'm going to hurt you.

16:13.400 --> 16:14.730
[laughter]

16:14.730 --> 16:17.330
So, that kind--you know
that little thing you did

16:17.330 --> 16:18.670
with the glue stick,
and you did

16:18.670 --> 16:20.930
the little scissors,
you did this, you did that.

16:20.930 --> 16:22.970
I'm telling you,
we have a little list.

16:22.970 --> 16:25.330
I'll hit you in the head.
- [laughing]

16:25.330 --> 16:27.270
- I'll kick you in the ass.

16:27.270 --> 16:29.630
I'll knock you down.
I'll trip you.

16:29.630 --> 16:31.430
Imagine those are laid out
in front of you

16:31.430 --> 16:32.600
as I say this.
[Alyson laughing]

16:32.600 --> 16:34.230
Here's the problem.
- Okay.

16:34.230 --> 16:35.930
- You know,
we've hung out with you.

16:35.930 --> 16:38.830
In hotel rooms, with you
doing this stuff for us.

16:38.830 --> 16:40.300
Amazing stuff.

16:40.300 --> 16:42.630
And there's a--
kind of a shortcut

16:42.630 --> 16:46.670
Teller and I use talking about
juggling and magic.

16:46.670 --> 16:49.330
Because juggling, you say
you're gonna do something

16:49.330 --> 16:50.630
and you do it.

16:50.630 --> 16:52.700
And in magic, you say
you're gonna do something

16:52.700 --> 16:54.130
and you don't.

16:54.130 --> 16:55.730
We think--

16:55.730 --> 16:57.670
we know you can control
a card anywhere.

16:57.670 --> 16:59.170
We know once
I've picked a card,

16:59.170 --> 17:00.830
you can put it
wherever you want.

17:00.830 --> 17:03.630
We know you could put
that card where you want.

17:03.630 --> 17:05.670
We kinda-sorta
watched you do it.

17:05.670 --> 17:10.369
And then, and this is
the weirdest bust we've done,

17:10.369 --> 17:12.869
we think you actually did it.

17:12.869 --> 17:14.900
We don't think
there was a trick.

17:14.900 --> 17:17.470
We think you knew
the location of the card,

17:17.470 --> 17:19.630
and you've been practicing
since you were 18,

17:19.630 --> 17:22.470
'cause you reached in
and grabbed the [bleep] thing.

17:22.470 --> 17:23.470
[laughter]

17:23.470 --> 17:26.130
We think you actually did

17:26.130 --> 17:28.470
what you said
you were going to do,

17:28.470 --> 17:31.430
and therefore,
although you blew our minds

17:31.430 --> 17:33.270
and amazed us,

17:33.270 --> 17:34.730
you did not fool us.

17:34.730 --> 17:38.170
We think you are that
[bleep] good.

17:38.170 --> 17:39.270
[laughter]

17:39.270 --> 17:41.530
So go ahead, tell me
you're not that good.

17:41.530 --> 17:43.130
- So you think
that I've been locked up

17:43.130 --> 17:45.500
for 20 years practicing,
and that I could...

17:45.500 --> 17:48.730
precision dribble
and catch any card that I want

17:48.730 --> 17:50.600
from anywhere in the deck?
- Uh...

17:50.600 --> 17:52.270
Kinda-sorta-ish, yeah.

17:52.270 --> 17:53.870
[laughter]

17:53.870 --> 17:55.230
- You're 100% right.

17:55.230 --> 17:56.630
- Wow!

17:56.630 --> 17:59.270
[cheers and applause]

17:59.270 --> 18:01.530
- Thank you so much.
- You're so good, baby.

18:01.530 --> 18:03.570
You're so good.
- Thank you so much.

18:03.570 --> 18:05.000
Thank you,
you guys are the best.

18:05.000 --> 18:06.230
- Aww!
- So good!

18:06.230 --> 18:07.700
- Thank you, guys.
- That was incredible!

18:07.700 --> 18:10.770
- He's better than you think,
I'm telling you that.

18:10.770 --> 18:12.700
- Kostya Kimlat!

18:12.700 --> 18:14.170
- Thank you very much!

18:14.170 --> 18:16.870
Thank you, guys!
Thank you!

18:16.870 --> 18:19.130
- More magic coming up,
including something

18:19.130 --> 18:21.800
from entertainment's
greatest duo:

18:21.800 --> 18:23.700
Penn and Teller!

18:23.700 --> 18:25.500
[cheers and applause]

18:25.500 --> 18:28.500
<i>[jazz music]</i>

18:31.230 --> 18:34.170
<i>[jazz music]</i>

18:34.170 --> 18:37.130
[cheers and applause]

18:37.130 --> 18:39.030
- Welcome back to "Fool Us"!

18:39.030 --> 18:41.370
We've seen one fooler
so far tonight.

18:41.370 --> 18:44.470
Let's go for two,
as we meet our next magician.

18:46.500 --> 18:47.530
- I am from Sweden.

18:47.530 --> 18:48.530
I am a magician,

18:48.530 --> 18:50.270
comedian, and singer.

18:50.270 --> 18:52.900
<i>When I was a kid,
if they would say go left,</i>

18:52.900 --> 18:54.400
<i>I would go right.</i>

18:54.400 --> 18:57.870
You know we have the phrasing,
"color outside the lines"?

18:57.870 --> 18:59.570
<i>Yeah, I was that kid.</i>

18:59.570 --> 19:01.330
<i>I grew up
in a little small village.</i>

19:01.330 --> 19:04.200
<i>We had only one gas station
and one store.</i>

19:04.200 --> 19:06.500
Nobody knew anything
about magic.

19:06.500 --> 19:10.370
<i>I actually found a magic book
in our bookshelf at home.</i>

19:10.370 --> 19:14.570
<i>I read that book so hard,
it fell apart.</i>

19:14.570 --> 19:16.470
<i>Today, I travel
all around the world</i>

19:16.470 --> 19:19.570
<i>and doing my magic
and comedy and music.</i>

19:19.570 --> 19:23.500
<i>If you are a comedy magician
and your jokes doesn't work,</i>

19:23.500 --> 19:26.100
<i>you really have to have
good magic.</i>

19:26.100 --> 19:30.370
<i>And if I fail in both,
I can sing a song.</i>

19:30.370 --> 19:33.930
[cheers and applause]

19:33.930 --> 19:39.070
- All the way from Sweden,
here is Hakan Berg!

19:39.070 --> 19:42.100
[cheers and applause]

19:42.100 --> 19:45.370
[guitar strums]
- ♪ It's impossible ♪

19:45.370 --> 19:48.070
♪ In our mind ♪

19:48.070 --> 19:53.670
♪ I can't believe it
we are so blind ♪

19:53.670 --> 19:59.200
♪ We gotta believe in magic ♪

19:59.200 --> 20:04.500
♪ Don't get lost
in this confusion ♪

20:04.500 --> 20:09.670
♪ We gotta believe
